  "messages": [
    {
      "id": "b293b11cf57ac9ebe1e40201f7359c65de259083",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 2,
        "name": "Jenkins",
        "username": "hudson",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2012-08-21 05:46:40.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nBuild Started http://build.whamcloud.com/job/lustre-reviews/8530/ ",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "ea51fe5aa1a2a78e971e849a513b4673f9609e5a",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2012-08-21 06:20:11.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nIt would be best if the get_mmp_update_interval() code could work with both the old and new e2fsprogs output. This would avoid breakage for test environments that do not have the latest version installed (e.g. developer or external testing).\n\nSomething like the following should work:\n\n    awk '/update.interval/i { print $NF }'\n\nBut I'm not at a system where I can verify the exact syntax. IIRC, $NF is the number of fields, so it should print the last item in the line, and /i will make a case-insensitive search.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "9d3e6e57906969b97164f2a92ec81aaa19293b43",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 2,
        "name": "Jenkins",
        "username": "hudson",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2012-08-21 06:25:24.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: Verified\n\nBuild Successful \n \nhttp://build.whamcloud.com/job/lustre-reviews/8530/ : SUCCESS",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "0b7e382da544e521c656426dba172271f1ffc882",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 131,
        "name": "Jian Yu",
        "email": "yujian@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "yujian"
      },
      "date": "2012-08-21 07:42:19.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n> But I'm not at a system where I can verify the exact syntax. IIRC, $NF is the number of fields, so it should print the last > item in the line, and /i will make a case-insensitive search.\n\nThanks for the suggestions.\n\nI just verified the command with e2fsprogs version 1.42.3.wc3 and 1.41.90.wc3 separately. $NF is correct, but /i is not an awk syntax. Per the link of http://www.gnu.org/software/gawk/manual/html_node/Case_002dsensitivity.html , I changed the command as follows:\n\nawk 'tolower($0) ~ /update.interval/ { print $NF }'\n\nIt works correctly on both versions.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
